---
import ServicePage from "../../layouts/ServicePage.astro";
import heroImg from "../../assets/office/hero-2108.jpg";
---
<ServicePage
  title="Emergency Dentist in Bayside, Queens NY | Thrive Dental"
  description="Emergency dentist in Bayside, Queens NY — same-day appointments for toothaches, broken teeth, lost crowns, and dental injuries. Call now: (718) 225-6677."
  category="Emergency Care"
  categoryHref="/services"
  h1="Emergency Dentist in Bayside, Queens NY"
  subtitle="Dental emergencies can't wait. We reserve same-day appointments daily for urgent care — call us immediately and we'll get you seen as fast as possible."
  heroImg={heroImg}
  overviewTitle="We're here when it matters most."
  overviewText="A dental emergency is any situation causing severe pain, significant bleeding, a knocked-out or broken tooth, a suspected infection, or a lost restoration that leaves a tooth exposed and vulnerable. Unlike many practices that tell patients to 'call in the morning,' we reserve time slots every single day specifically for urgent care — because dental problems that are left to wait almost always get worse, and more expensive to treat."
  overviewExtra="If you're searching for an emergency dentist in Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, Little Neck, or anywhere in Northeast Queens, call our office directly at (718) 225-6677. We treat dental emergencies including severe toothaches, abscesses, knocked-out teeth, broken or cracked teeth, lost crowns or fillings, soft tissue injuries, and broken orthodontic appliances. For patients who call before noon, same-day appointments are almost always available. After-hours dental emergencies: call the same number and our voicemail will provide instructions for reaching us. Do not suffer through dental pain — the sooner we see you, the more treatment options we have and the less invasive the solution will be."
  benefits={[
    {
      icon: `<rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="18" rx="2" ry="2"/><line x1="16" y1="2" x2="16" y2="6"/><line x1="8" y1="2" x2="8" y2="6"/><line x1="3" y1="10" x2="21" y2="10"/>`,
      title: 'Same-Day Appointments',
      desc: 'We hold daily slots for urgent cases. Call us first — most emergency patients are seen within hours of calling.',
    },
    {
      icon: `<path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/>`,
      title: 'All Emergencies Treated',
      desc: 'Toothaches, broken teeth, lost crowns, abscesses, knocked-out teeth — our team handles the full range of dental emergencies.',
    },
    {
      icon: `<circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M8 14s1.5 2 4 2 4-2 4-2"/><line x1="9" y1="9" x2="9.01" y2="9"/><line x1="15" y1="9" x2="15.01" y2="9"/>`,
      title: 'Pain Relief First',
      desc: 'Our first priority is getting you out of pain quickly. We diagnose, provide immediate relief, and then discuss your longer-term treatment plan.',
    },
  ]}
  faq={[
    {
      q: 'What counts as a dental emergency?',
      a: 'Call us immediately for: severe toothache, knocked-out or broken tooth, lost crown or filling, dental abscess (swelling or pus near a tooth), broken orthodontic wire causing injury, or uncontrolled bleeding after an extraction. When in doubt — call us.',
    },
    {
      q: 'What should I do if a tooth gets knocked out?',
      a: 'Pick up the tooth by the crown (not the root), rinse it gently without scrubbing, and try to reinsert it into the socket. If that\'s not possible, store it in milk or between your cheek and gum. Call us immediately — a knocked-out tooth has the best chance of being saved if treated within 30–60 minutes.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Can you see me the same day?',
      a: 'Yes — we reserve emergency slots every day for urgent situations. Call (718) 225-6677 as soon as possible. The sooner we know, the sooner we can get you in.',
    },
    {
      q: 'I have a dental abscess. Is it dangerous?',
      a: 'A dental abscess can become serious if the infection spreads. Signs requiring immediate ER care: fever above 101°F, difficulty swallowing or breathing, significant facial swelling, or feeling very ill. For a painful swelling without these symptoms, call us for a same-day appointment.',
    },
    {
      q: 'My crown fell off. What do I do?',
      a: 'Keep the crown if you find it, avoid chewing on that side, and call us. We can often re-cement or replace it quickly. Dental cement from the drugstore can serve as a temporary measure to protect the exposed tooth until we see you.',
    },
  ]}
  related={[
    { href: '/services/root-canal-therapy', label: 'Root Canal Therapy' },
    { href: '/services/dental-crowns',      label: 'Dental Crowns' },
    { href: '/services/dental-implants',    label: 'Dental Implants' },
  ]}
  relatedPosts={[
    { href: '/blog/dental-emergency-what-to-do', title: 'Dental Emergency? Here\'s What to Do', description: 'Knocked-out tooth, severe toothache, broken crown — a step-by-step guide for the most common dental emergencies.' },
  ]}
  ctaHeading="In pain right now? Call us."
>
  <section class="bg-red-50 border-y border-red-100 py-12">
    <div class="container-slim text-center">
      <p class="text-[11px] font-black uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-red-600 mb-3">Dental Emergency?</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Call us right now.</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 mb-6 max-w-md mx-auto">Don't wait for a callback form. Call our office directly for the fastest response. If it's a life-threatening emergency, call 911.</p>
      <a href="tel:+1-718-225-6677" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-red-600 px-8 py-4 text-sm font-bold text-white hover:bg-red-700 transition-colors no-underline shadow-lg shadow-red-500/20">
        <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07A19.5 19.5 0 0 1 4.99 12 19.79 19.79 0 0 1 1.95 3.42 2 2 0 0 1 3.93 1.25h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72c.127.96.361 1.903.7 2.81a2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L8.09 9a16 16 0 0 0 6.91 6.91l1.27-1.27a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45c.907.339 1.85.573 2.81.7A2 2 0 0 1 22 16.92z"/></svg>
        (718) 225-6677
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</ServicePage>
